  <h2>What is Mama Circle?</h2>
  <p>
    Mama Circle is a grassroots, community-led initiative. It exists to gently connect mothers who wish to support each other with honesty, softness, and care.
  </p>
  <p>
    This is not a company, coaching service, or moderated platform. You are witnessing, or joining, a self-organized collective of mamas supporting mamas through the quiet signal of <span class="hashtag">#mamacircle ðŸ’ž</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>What personal data do we collect?</h2>
  <p>
    This website does not track you. We don't use cookies, analytics, or automated data collection.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you choose to fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdBmw7GZ8UI61lRiiASpiIHP8Niuyj2b332ZbgEePJ4PiJiZg/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Circle message form (opens in new tab)">Circle message form</a>, you may share your name, general location, and a message. These are published only with your consent.
  </p>

  <h2>How is your data used?</h2>
  <p>
    Messages submitted via the form may be featured on the website as part of the Circle, to let other mamas feel seen, held, and reminded they're not alone.
  </p>
  <p>
    You do not need to list yourself or share any contact info. All messages are optional and softly offered.
  </p>
  <p>
    Want to update or remove your message? You can just <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdBmw7GZ8UI61lRiiASpiIHP8Niuyj2b332ZbgEePJ4PiJiZg/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="go to the form again and update it (opens in new tab)">go to the form again and update it</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Community & Safety</h2>
  <p>
    Mama Circle is not moderated, it relies on trust, shared values, and mutual care.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>No accounts or logins are needed. You can browse anonymously.</li>
    <li>All contact is voluntary. No one is expected to reply or engage.</li>
    <li>We do not vet or verify participants. Everyone appears in good faith.</li>
    <li>If you experience harm or see the hashtag misused, please <a href="mailto:hello@mamacircle.me">report it to us</a>.</li>
    <li>We encourage everyone to read and honor our <a href="/code-of-care">Code of Care</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>GDPR & Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    We respect your privacy. Under the GDPR and global data laws, you may access, change, or request deletion of any personal data you've shared with us.
  </p>

  <h2>Need help?</h2>
  <p>
    Always feel free to reach out to us at: <code>hello@mamacircle.me</code>.
  </p>
  <p>
    We are always learning. If you have ideas to make Mama Circle more inclusive, accessible, or safe, we welcome your thoughts.
  </p>

